Bring @water{2%cups} and a large pinch of @salt{} to boil in a #small pot{}.
Once boiling, add the @Jasmine Rice{1%cup}, cover, and reduce to a low simmer
for ~{15-20%minutes}, until tender.

Wash and dry all produce. Trim and halve the @Baby Bok Choy{4} lengthwise.
Thinly slice the bok choy widthwise into thin strips. Thinly slice the
@Scallions{4}, keeping the greens and whites separate. Peel and mince the
@Ginger{2%thumbs}. Mince the @Garlic{4%cloves}.

Combine @Soy Sauce{4%Tablespoons}, @Hoisin Sauce{2%Tablespoons},
@Honey{3%Tablespoons}, half the ginger, and half the garlic in a #medium bowl{}.
Add the @Beef Tenderloin Tips{16%ounce} to the marinade and toss to coat.

> If you have extra time, let the beef sit. The more time, the better!

Heat a drizzle of @Olive Oil{} in a #large pan{} over high heat. Working in
batches, sear the beef tips about ~{1%minute} per side, until browned.
Remove from the pan and set aside.

Add the scallion whites, remaining ginger, remaining garlic, and a drizzle of
oil to the same pan over medium heat. Cook, tossing, for about ~{1%minute},
until fragrant. Add the bok choy and cook, tossing, for ~{3-4%minutes},
until tender. Season with @salt{} and @Pepper{}. Return the beef to the pan
along with the marinade from the bowl and let bubble until sauce is thickened
and reduced. Season with salt and pepper.

> If you like your stir-fry sweeter, you can add more hoisin or honey.

Serve the stir-fry on a bed of rice. Sprinkle with the reserved scallion
greens and @Sesame Seeds{2%tablepoons} and dig in!